The paper addresses the problem of counting the number of strings in a collection, which is a common problem in information retrieval and data mining. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.IR (Information Retrieval). The paper also discusses the implementation and comparison of different solutions, which involves data structures and algorithms, making cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.CC (Computational Complexity) likely categories as well. Additionally, the paper mentions compressibility properties of the data structures, which relates to cs.DB (Databases) and cs.LG (Machine Learning).
